Look at the binary presentation of "num+1", you will find that binary value will append "1" when the tree go right, append "0" when the tree go left. With this feature, we can do a top down search without initialization.

We can also do it without using binary feature. We notice that even number is always on the right branch, odd number is always on the left branch, using this feature, we can reversely find the path of the number in the tree. Reversing this path and we will have the top-down path.

```
    def find(self, target: int) -> bool:
        tmp=bin(target+1)[3:]
        node=self.root
        for t in tmp:
            if t=='0':
                if not node.left:
                    return False
                node=node.left
            elif t=='1':
                if not node.right:
                    return False
                node=node.right
        return True
